Don't push me,

258
00:14:09,996 --> 00:14:11,706
and I won't push you.

259
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:29,909
Zoe, Wash gonna straighten
this boat out before we get flattened?

260
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,539
Like a downy feather, sir.

261
00:14:31,664 --> 00:14:33,562
No one flies like my mister.

262
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:43,798
River.

263
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:45,265
I know.

264
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:48,036
We're going for a ride.

265
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,048
Hey, little one.

266
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:12,995
Understand your part in all this?

267
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:16,414
Do you?

268
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:19,960
This is what I do, darling.

269
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:25,006
This is what I do.

270
00:15:27,594 --> 00:15:29,010
Let's move, people.

271
00:15:30,304 --> 00:15:32,722
Quit fiddling. Want the boat
running smooth when we get back.

272
00:15:32,807 --> 00:15:34,057
Have faith, Captain.

273
00:15:34,142 --> 00:15:35,475
Not today.

274
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:38,352
Pair of clips in the rear hatch.

275
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,889
We should hit town right
during Sunday worship.

276
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:43,609
Won't be any crowds.

277
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:45,943
Well if Fanty and Mingo
are right about the payroll,

278
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:48,071
this could look to be a sunny day for us.

279
00:15:48,155 --> 00:15:50,072
River, stay behind the others.

280
00:15:50,158 --> 00:15:52,900
If there's fighting,
drop to the floor or run away.

281
00:15:54,202 --> 00:15:56,203
It's okay to leave them to die.

282
00:15:56,538 --> 00:16:00,042
Doctor, I'm taking your sister
under my protection here.

283
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:02,636
If anything happens to her,
anything at all,

284
00:16:02,669 --> 00:16:05,547
I swear to you,
I will get very choked up.

285
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:07,332
Honestly, there could be tears.

286
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:18,187
Don't mind the Captain none, Simon.

287
00:16:18,513 --> 00:16:20,461
I know he'll look out for her.

288
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:23,315
They'll be back before you can spit.

289
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:28,445
Well, not that you spit.

290
00:16:34,409 --> 00:16:37,162
What are we hoping to find here
that equals the worth of a turd?

291
00:16:37,245 --> 00:16:40,039
Security payroll.
Alliance don't have the manpower

292
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:42,709
to enforce the peace on every outer-rim planet.

293
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:45,754
They hire out to the private firms,
who will not work for credit.

294
00:16:45,837 --> 00:16:49,508
They get paid in cashy money, which,
once a month, rests here.

295
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:51,677
Don't that lead back to the Alliance, anyhow?

296
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:54,596
No private firm would ever report the theft
of their own payroll.

297
00:16:54,681 --> 00:16:57,849
They'd appear weak,
might lose their contract.

298
00:16:57,933 --> 00:17:00,011
Yeah, we're as ghosts in this.

299
00:17:00,037 --> 00:17:01,943
Won't but rattle the floor.

300
00:17:02,105 --> 00:17:04,690
Shiny. Let's be bad guys.

301
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:08,317
Hands and knees and heads bowed down!
Everybody, down!

302
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:20,564
Looks like this is the place.

303
00:17:20,914 --> 00:17:24,058
You all wanna be looking very intently
at your own belly buttons.

304
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:27,796
I see a head start to rise,
violence is going to ensue.

305
00:17:29,257 --> 00:17:30,882
Probably guessed we mean
to be thieving here,

306
00:17:30,967 --> 00:17:33,134
but what we're after is not yours so...

307
00:17:33,885 --> 00:17:35,787
let's have no undue fussing.

308
00:17:36,638 --> 00:17:37,972
She's locked up.

309
00:18:24,729 --> 00:18:27,189
Do you know what the definition
of a hero is?

310
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:30,107
Someone who gets other people killed.

311
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:32,152
You can look it up later.

312
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:37,124
Big happy family.

313
00:18:46,709 --> 00:18:50,211
At last, we can retire and give up
this life of crime.

314
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:57,760
Hey!

315
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:02,265
You all are Browncoats, eh?
Fought for independence?

316
00:19:02,349 --> 00:19:04,392
Petty thieving ain't exactly soldiers work.

317
00:19:04,477 --> 00:19:06,798
War's long done.
We're all just folk now.

318
00:19:07,722 --> 00:19:08,796
Listen up!

319
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:11,148
We are coming down to empty that vault!

320
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:14,051
You have to give me
your authorization password!

321
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,281
Okay.

322
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:35,548
I'm telling you I heard it.
Repeater.

323
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:37,804
Did sound somewhat like gun blast.

324
00:19:37,827 --> 00:19:39,710
Maybe you ought run tell Lawman.

325
00:19:42,682 --> 00:19:43,963
What the hell is up?

326
00:19:44,189 --> 00:19:45,374
You all right?

327
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:47,810
What's going on?

328
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:50,521
Reavers.

329
00:19:57,238 --> 00:20:00,865
The leg is good. It'll bleed plenty
and we avoid any necessary organs.

330
00:20:00,950 --> 00:20:02,284
I was thinking more of a graze.

331
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:04,407
No, you don't want it
to look like you just gave up.

332
00:20:04,412 --> 00:20:05,452
No, I get that.

333
00:20:05,538 --> 00:20:06,913
Mal!

334
00:20:06,998 --> 00:20:09,249
Every heist,
he's got to start yelling my name.

335
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,255
Mal!

336
00:20:10,779 --> 00:20:11,834
Reavers!

337
00:20:12,545 --> 00:20:14,971
The girl's pitching a fit.
They're here or they're coming soon.

338
00:20:15,256 --> 00:20:16,631
Get on the Mule.

339
00:20:17,215 --> 00:20:18,909
What's that?
Does that lock from the inside?

340
00:20:18,932 --> 00:20:19,593
Yes.

341
00:20:19,594 --> 00:20:22,053
Get everyone upstairs.
You get them down here and you seal it.

342
00:20:22,137 --> 00:20:24,230
As long as you got air, you don't open up,
you understand?

343
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:25,414
But...

344
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:27,792
Get them inside the vault!

345
00:20:28,344 --> 00:20:29,894
You see them?

346
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:31,104
Zoe, take the wheel!

347
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:32,564
Anybody see them?

348
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:40,238
Take me with you!

349
00:20:40,323 --> 00:20:41,990
Get back in the vault with the others.

350
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:43,282
I can't stay here!
Please!

351
00:20:43,366 --> 00:20:44,992
It's too many.
Move ahead.

352
00:20:45,277 --> 00:20:46,382
Please!

353
00:20:49,205 --> 00:20:50,205
Please!

354
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:23,573
Faster! Faster!
Faster would be better!

355
00:21:32,540 --> 00:21:34,260
How come they ain't blowing us out the air?

356
00:21:34,292 --> 00:21:37,170
They wanna run us down.
The up-close kill.

357
00:21:38,756 --> 00:21:40,965
They want us alive when they eat us.

358
00:21:41,424 --> 00:21:45,302
Boy, sure would be nice if we had
some grenades, don't you think?

359
00:21:46,931 --> 00:21:48,973
Wash, baby, can you hear me?

360
00:21:49,057 --> 00:21:50,099
We're moments from air.

361
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:51,305
You got somebody behind you?

362
00:21:51,309 --> 00:21:52,477
Reavers.

363
00:21:54,771 --> 00:21:55,814
Kaylee!

364
00:21:55,897 --> 00:21:56,981
Heat her up.
We got Reavers.

365
00:22:01,737 --> 00:22:03,404
We're not gonna get to you in time.

366
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:04,823
Keep moving, honey.

367
00:22:04,906 --> 00:22:06,490
We're coming to you.

368
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,000
Where's my clips?

369
00:22:15,084 --> 00:22:16,209
Rear hatch.

370
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:28,137
Jayne!

371
00:22:31,808 --> 00:22:33,183
I won't get ate!

372
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:36,709
You shoot me if they take me!

373
00:22:37,334 --> 00:22:39,064
Well, don't shoot me first!

374
00:22:57,751 --> 00:22:59,711
Get some distance on them.

375
00:22:59,795 --> 00:23:02,630
You come to the flats,
I want you to swing round.

376
00:23:02,964 --> 00:23:04,883
We're gonna try a Barn Swallow.

377
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,925
Simon! Open her up!

378
00:23:12,016 --> 00:23:13,474
They're closing on us!

379
00:23:13,558 --> 00:23:15,769
Those rocks, give them a taste.

380
00:23:31,367 --> 00:23:33,744
Okay, baby, we talked this through.

381
00:23:36,999 --> 00:23:38,374
Talking ain't doing.

382
00:24:18,915 --> 00:24:20,541
River?

383
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,376
I swallowed a bug.

384
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,541
Are you okay?

385
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:30,343
Is he okay?

386
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:45,825
<i>We all here?
What's going on?</i>

387
00:24:46,317 --> 00:24:47,609
Hello?

388
00:24:50,114 --> 00:24:51,405
No casualties.

389
00:24:51,699 --> 00:24:52,740
Anybody following?

390
00:24:52,825 --> 00:24:54,159
<i>Nice flying, baby.</i>

391
00:24:54,242 --> 00:24:56,702
That's a negative.
Clean getaway.

392
00:24:57,078 --> 00:24:58,699
Set course for Beaumonde.

393
00:24:58,923 --> 00:25:01,198
First thing, I want this body...

394
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:02,500
Simon!

395
00:25:05,503 --> 00:25:07,255
You son of a whore.
I'm a hair's breadth

396
00:25:07,338 --> 00:25:08,673
from riddling you with holes, Doctor.

397
00:25:08,757 --> 00:25:10,842
One simple job!
She'll be fine!

398
00:25:10,925 --> 00:25:12,176
She is fine!

399
00:25:12,260 --> 00:25:14,345
Except for being still crazy,
she's a picture of health!

400
00:25:14,430 --> 00:25:16,685
Wasn't for River,
we'd probably be left there.

401
00:25:16,810 --> 00:25:18,207
She felt them coming.

402
00:25:18,349 --> 00:25:20,434
Never again.
Do you understand me?

403
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:23,313
Seems I remember a talk about you
giving orders on my boat.

404
00:25:23,396 --> 00:25:24,939
Well, we're off your boat.

405
00:25:25,023 --> 00:25:27,442
Just as soon as River gets her
share of the bounty.

406
00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:28,942
Let's not do anything hasty...

407
00:25:28,943 --> 00:25:30,319
No, shiny!

408
00:25:30,613 --> 00:25:32,213
We'll be on Beaumonde in 10 hours' time,

409
00:25:32,239 --> 00:25:35,115
you can pick up your earnings
and be on your merry.

410
00:25:35,409 --> 00:25:38,243
Meantime, you do your job.

411
00:25:39,121 --> 00:25:40,704
Patch up my crew.

412
00:25:43,041 --> 00:25:44,666
He didn't lie down.

413
00:25:46,461 --> 00:25:48,128
They never lie down.

414
00:25:57,096 --> 00:25:59,265
No, I think things will glide
a deal smoother for us

415
00:25:59,349 --> 00:26:01,267
without River and Simon on board,

416
00:26:01,352 --> 00:26:03,269
but how long do you think they'll last?

417
00:26:03,354 --> 00:26:04,394
Doc made his call.

418
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:05,480
Yeah.

419
00:26:05,564 --> 00:26:07,397
They's as babes in a basket
when we took them in.

420
00:26:07,482 --> 00:26:09,275
We sheltered them plenty.

421
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:12,694
Man has to cut loose,
learn to stand on his own.

422
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:16,365
Like that man back in town?

423
00:26:19,327 --> 00:26:20,744
I had to shoot him.

424
00:26:20,828 --> 00:26:22,747
What the Reavers would've done
to him before they killed him...

425
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:25,250
I know.
That was a piece of mercy.

426
00:26:26,251 --> 00:26:29,211
But before that, him begging us
to bring him along.

427
00:26:30,381 --> 00:26:33,258
We couldn't take the weight.
Would've slowed us down.

428
00:26:33,342 --> 00:26:34,759
You know that for certain?

429
00:26:34,843 --> 00:26:36,677
Mule won't run with five.

430
00:26:37,346 --> 00:26:40,856
I should've dumped the girl?
Or you? Or Jayne?

431
00:26:41,224 --> 00:26:42,517
Oh, Jayne...

432
00:26:43,519 --> 00:26:44,935
You could've tossed the payload.

433
00:26:45,019 --> 00:26:46,311
Tossed the...

434
00:26:47,522 --> 00:26:51,233
Zoe, I got bits falling off my ship,
I got a crew ain't been paid,

435
00:26:51,317 --> 00:26:54,278
and, oh, yeah, a powerful need to eat
sometime this month.

436
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:56,458
We tell Fanty and Mingo
we skunked the job,

437
00:26:56,531 --> 00:26:58,432
what do think they'll do to us?

438
00:27:00,368 --> 00:27:02,287
We're close to gone out here.

439
00:27:03,454 --> 00:27:05,873
We get a job, we got to make good.

440
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:09,085
Sir, I don't disagree on any particular point.

441
00:27:10,837 --> 00:27:12,005
It's just,

442
00:27:15,217 --> 00:27:18,428
in the time of war, we would've never
left a man stranded.

443
00:27:19,846 --> 00:27:21,556
Maybe that's why we lost.

444
00:27:30,941 --> 00:27:32,607
That was close.

445
00:27:34,944 --> 00:27:36,320
I do not get it.

446
00:27:37,197 --> 00:27:38,990
How's a guy get so wrong?

447
00:27:39,074 --> 00:27:40,863
Cutting on his own face,

448
00:27:41,087 --> 00:27:42,800
raping and murdering.

449
00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:47,457
I'll kill a man in a fair fight,

450
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:50,751
or if I think he's gonna start a fair fight,

451
00:27:51,627 --> 00:27:53,076
or if he bothers me,

452
00:27:53,301 --> 00:27:54,997
or if there's a woman,

453
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:57,277
or if I'm getting paid.

454
00:27:58,402 --> 00:28:00,251
Mostly only when I'm getting paid.

455
00:28:01,596 --> 00:28:04,106
These Reavers, the last 10 years,

456
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:06,826
they show up like
the bogeyman from stories.

457
00:28:08,228 --> 00:28:09,660
Eating people alive?

458
00:28:10,184 --> 00:28:11,645
Where does that get fun?

459
00:28:13,107 --> 00:28:15,442
Shepherd Book said they was men who just

460
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:17,228
reached the edge of space,

461
00:28:17,553 --> 00:28:20,647
saw a vasty nothingness
and went bibbledy over it.

462
00:28:21,075 --> 00:28:22,075
Oh, hell.

463
00:28:23,868 --> 00:28:25,452
I've been to the edge.

464
00:28:26,121 --> 00:28:27,198
Just looked like...

465
00:28:28,522 --> 00:28:29,823
more space.

466
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,376
I don't know.

467
00:28:32,461 --> 00:28:34,836
It can get awful lonely in the black.

468
00:28:36,131 --> 00:28:37,632
Like to get addlepated ourselves,

469
00:28:37,715 --> 00:28:39,634
we stay on this boat much longer.

470
00:28:40,344 --> 00:28:42,845
Captain will drive us all off, one by one.

471
00:28:43,513 --> 00:28:45,515
Just like Simon and River.

472
00:28:47,308 --> 00:28:48,768
Just like Inara.

473
00:28:50,019 --> 00:28:52,896
<i>Kaylee, are you ever going
to put that capture down?</i>

474
00:28:52,980 --> 00:28:55,525
<i>We got to have records of everything, Inara.</i>

475
00:28:55,608 --> 00:28:59,487
<i>A bona fide companion entertained clients
on this very ship.</i>

476
00:28:59,988 --> 00:29:01,489
<i>In this very bed.</i>

477
00:29:01,573 --> 00:29:03,365
<i>Well, I can't do my work here.</i>

478
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:05,451
<i>And I don't think the Captain approves.</i>

479
00:29:05,536 --> 00:29:07,119
<i>The Captain wants you to stay...</i>

480
00:29:07,203 --> 00:29:10,580
<i>That man doesn't know what he wants.
I don't have time to...</i>

481
00:29:44,740 --> 00:29:47,285
Don't talk to the barkers, talk to the captains.

482
00:29:47,368 --> 00:29:50,746
You look the captain in the eye.
Know who you're dealing with.

483
00:29:51,330 --> 00:29:52,874
I wish there was...

484
00:29:56,377 --> 00:29:58,145
You shouldn't ought to be so clean.

485
00:29:58,963 --> 00:30:01,866
It's a dead giveaway you don't belong,
you always got to be tidy.

486
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:04,469
Don't pay anybody in advance.

487
00:30:06,137 --> 00:30:08,597
And don't ride in anything with
a Capissen 38 engine,

488
00:30:08,682 --> 00:30:10,482
they fall right out of the sky.

489
00:30:11,393 --> 00:30:12,527
Kaylee.

490
00:30:24,155 --> 00:30:26,365
River, do you want to stay with them?

491
00:30:27,992 --> 00:30:29,576
It isn't safe.

492
00:30:31,288 --> 00:30:32,288
No.

493
00:30:34,583 --> 00:30:36,709
I fear it isn't safe anymore.

494
00:30:39,212 --> 00:30:40,421
For them.

495
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:06,239
Kaylee, this is a place of business.
We can talk about Simon when...

496
00:31:06,323 --> 00:31:07,781
When he's four worlds away?

497
00:31:07,865 --> 00:31:10,201
Or the Alliance gets
a hold of him and River?

498
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:11,362
That ain't my worry.

499
00:31:11,386 --> 00:31:13,728
I got to finish this job
and get us another one.

500
00:31:13,788 --> 00:31:15,623
Can't do that carrying those two.

501
00:31:15,999 --> 00:31:17,875
How can you be so cold?

502
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:20,126
Captain didn't make them fugitives.

503
00:31:20,253 --> 00:31:22,320
But he could have made them family.

504
00:31:22,588 --> 00:31:25,383
Instead of keeping Simon
from seeing I was there.

505
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:28,911
When I carried such a torch,
when we could've...

506
00:31:29,596 --> 00:31:32,390
Going on a year now,
I ain't had nothing twixt my nethers

507
00:31:32,413 --> 00:31:33,857
weren't run on batteries.

508
00:31:34,142 --> 00:31:36,352
God! I can't know that!

509
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:38,604
I could stand to hear a little more.

510
00:31:39,272 --> 00:31:40,897
If you had a care for anybody's heart...

511
00:31:40,982 --> 00:31:42,607
You knew he was gonna leave.

512
00:31:42,692 --> 00:31:44,493
We never been
but a way station to those two.

513
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:46,194
And how do you know what he feels?

514
00:31:46,279 --> 00:31:49,240
He's got River to worry on,
but he still could've shown you...

515
00:31:49,324 --> 00:31:51,576
If I truly wanted someone bad enough,

516
00:31:51,660 --> 00:31:54,145
wouldn't be a thing in the 'verse
