00:49:21,291 --> 00:49:22,708
Only but a few hours out.

778
00:49:23,335 --> 00:49:26,338
Yeah, but, remember the part
where it's a trap?

779
00:49:26,547 --> 00:49:28,965
If that's the case,
then Inara's already caught in it.

780
00:49:29,050 --> 00:49:31,050
She wouldn't set us up willing.

781
00:49:31,260 --> 00:49:34,137
Might be we got a shot at seeing who's
turning these wheels.

782
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:35,221
We go in.

783
00:49:35,306 --> 00:49:38,641
But how can you be sure Inara
don't just wanna see you?

784
00:49:39,559 --> 00:49:41,978
Sometimes people have feelings.

785
00:49:42,146 --> 00:49:44,188
I'm referring here to people.

786
00:49:45,940 --> 00:49:48,068
You all were watching, I take it.

787
00:49:49,737 --> 00:49:50,737
Yes.

788
00:49:50,820 --> 00:49:51,820
Did you see us fight?

789
00:49:51,905 --> 00:49:52,905
No.

790
00:49:52,989 --> 00:49:54,074
Trap.

791
00:50:01,498 --> 00:50:05,335
We're about 70 miles from the Training House,
and nobody on radar.

792
00:50:05,418 --> 00:50:07,836
If the Alliance is about, they're laying low.

793
00:50:07,922 --> 00:50:09,088
They're about.

794
00:50:09,172 --> 00:50:11,173
Find us a home.
I'll take the shuttle a little closer.

795
00:50:11,257 --> 00:50:12,925
Zoe, ship is yours.

796
00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:15,512
Remember.
If anything happens to me,

797
00:50:15,596 --> 00:50:17,356
or if you don't hear from me within the hour,

798
00:50:17,389 --> 00:50:19,682
you take this ship and you come
and you rescue me.

799
00:50:19,766 --> 00:50:20,766
What?

800
00:50:21,393 --> 00:50:22,768
Risk my ship?

801
00:50:22,853 --> 00:50:24,019
I mean it.

802
00:50:24,105 --> 00:50:26,255
It's cold out there.
And I don't wanna get left.

803
00:50:43,708 --> 00:50:47,043
Dear Buddha, please bring me a pony,
and a plastic rocket, and...

804
00:50:47,128 --> 00:50:49,045
Mal!
What are you doing here?

805
00:50:49,630 --> 00:50:50,838
Well, you invited me.

806
00:50:50,922 --> 00:50:53,465
I never thought for a second
you'd be stupid enough to come.

807
00:50:53,550 --> 00:50:55,385
Well, that makes you kind of a tease,
doesn't it?

808
00:50:55,469 --> 00:50:57,387
You knew my invitation wasn't on the level.

809
00:50:57,471 --> 00:51:00,431
Which led me to conclude that
you must be in some trouble.

810
00:51:00,516 --> 00:51:02,266
I'm fine.
I'm giddy.

811
00:51:02,351 --> 00:51:04,768
For a woman schooled in telling a man
what he wants to hear,

812
00:51:04,853 --> 00:51:06,128
you ain't much of a liar.

813
00:51:06,152 --> 00:51:08,356
Mal, you cannot handle this man.

814
00:51:14,447 --> 00:51:15,572
I have to say, Captain,

815
00:51:15,655 --> 00:51:18,532
I'm impressed that you would come
for her yourself.

816
00:51:18,826 --> 00:51:21,952
And that you would make it this far,
in that outfit.

817
00:51:23,164 --> 00:51:25,414
I can be very graceful when I need to.

818
00:51:25,498 --> 00:51:26,875
I've no doubt.

819
00:51:28,293 --> 00:51:29,293
What are you doing?

820
00:51:29,378 --> 00:51:31,003
I'm praying for you, Mal.

821
00:51:31,713 --> 00:51:33,505
She's very thoughtful.

822
00:51:33,923 --> 00:51:36,885
But I mean it when I say
I've no intent to harm you.

823
00:51:37,677 --> 00:51:39,304
Speak your piece.

824
00:51:39,764 --> 00:51:41,597
I think you're beginning to understand

825
00:51:41,681 --> 00:51:43,641
how dangerous River Tam is.

826
00:51:44,018 --> 00:51:45,851
She is a mite unpredictable.

827
00:51:46,103 --> 00:51:47,978
Mood swings, of a sort.

828
00:51:48,063 --> 00:51:49,355
It's worse than you know.

829
00:51:49,440 --> 00:51:50,606
It usually is.

830
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:54,318
That girl will rain destruction down on
you and your ship.

831
00:51:55,695 --> 00:51:58,489
She is an albatross, Captain.

832
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:00,365
Way I remember it,

833
00:52:00,492 --> 00:52:03,827
albatross was a ship's good luck,
till some idiot killed it.

834
00:52:04,371 --> 00:52:07,039
Yes, I've read a poem.
Try not to faint.

835
00:52:07,583 --> 00:52:09,416
I've seen your war record.

836
00:52:10,376 --> 00:52:12,961
I know how you must feel
about the Alliance.

837
00:52:13,213 --> 00:52:14,297
You really don't.

838
00:52:14,380 --> 00:52:15,422
Fair to say.

839
00:52:16,175 --> 00:52:18,967
But I have to hope you understand,
you can't beat us.

840
00:52:19,052 --> 00:52:20,804
I got no need to beat you.

841
00:52:20,887 --> 00:52:22,137
I just want to go my way.

842
00:52:22,222 --> 00:52:23,722
And you can do that,

843
00:52:24,557 --> 00:52:27,601
once you let me take River Tam
back home.

844
00:52:31,315 --> 00:52:33,858
No, no.
You're working this deal all crabbed.

845
00:52:33,943 --> 00:52:35,275
You got to open with payment.

846
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:36,652
That is a trap.

847
00:52:36,737 --> 00:52:40,322
I offer money, you'll play the man of honor
and take umbrage.

848
00:52:40,574 --> 00:52:43,159
I ask you to do what is right,
you'll play the brigand.

849
00:52:43,244 --> 00:52:45,744
I have no stomach for games.

850
00:52:46,288 --> 00:52:48,289
I already know you will not see reason.

851
00:52:48,373 --> 00:52:49,974
The Alliance wanted to show me a reason,

852
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:52,210
they shouldn't have sent an assassin.

853
00:52:58,425 --> 00:53:01,552
I have a warship in deep orbit, Captain.

854
00:53:02,179 --> 00:53:05,764
We locked on to Serenity's pulse beacon
the moment you hit atmo.

855
00:53:05,891 --> 00:53:07,851
I can speak a word and send a missile

856
00:53:07,934 --> 00:53:10,686
to that exact location inside of three minutes.

857
00:53:10,771 --> 00:53:11,938
You do that,

858
00:53:13,023 --> 00:53:15,900
you'd best make peace
with your dear and fluffy lord.

859
00:53:19,655 --> 00:53:20,905
Pulse beacon.

860
00:53:21,155 --> 00:53:25,117
Advice from an old tracker.
You want to find someone, use your eyes.

861
00:53:25,619 --> 00:53:27,871
How long do you think you can
really run from us?

862
00:53:27,954 --> 00:53:30,539
I never credited the Alliance with
an overabundance of brains.

863
00:53:30,623 --> 00:53:31,666
And if you're the best they got...

864
00:53:31,750 --> 00:53:32,876
Captain Reynolds,

865
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:35,711
I should tell you,
so that you don't waste your time,

866
00:53:35,795 --> 00:53:38,172
you can't make me angry.

867
00:53:38,257 --> 00:53:39,798
Please, spend an hour with him.

868
00:53:40,509 --> 00:53:43,302
I want to resolve this like civilized men.

869
00:53:44,387 --> 00:53:46,306
I'm not threatening you.

870
00:53:46,639 --> 00:53:48,141
I'm unarmed. Good.

871
00:53:53,230 --> 00:53:55,273
I am, of course, wearing full body armor.

872
00:53:55,356 --> 00:53:56,398
I am not a moron.

873
00:53:56,483 --> 00:53:57,692
Wait, just let...

874
00:54:25,887 --> 00:54:27,387
What, no backup?

875
00:54:27,889 --> 00:54:29,181
Making an awful ruckus.

876
00:54:29,266 --> 00:54:31,000
They'll come when they're needed.

877
00:54:31,184 --> 00:54:32,601
I'd start whistling.

878
00:54:32,728 --> 00:54:35,896
Captain, what do you think
is going to happen here?

879
00:55:22,735 --> 00:55:24,719
Nothing here is what it seems.

880
00:55:25,043 --> 00:55:27,097
He isn't the plucky hero.

881
00:55:27,907 --> 00:55:31,869
The Alliance isn't some evil empire.
This is not the grand arena.

882
00:55:32,079 --> 00:55:33,746
And that's not incense.

883
00:55:40,753 --> 00:55:41,920
Sir, can you hear me?

884
00:55:42,005 --> 00:55:44,548
Just a flash bomb.
Go. Go!

885
00:55:50,264 --> 00:55:51,764
What have you done to my shuttle?

886
00:55:51,849 --> 00:55:53,273
It's not your shuttle.

887
00:55:53,851 --> 00:55:55,527
Head east. Keep her low.

888
00:56:11,534 --> 00:56:13,369
Okay, forget the pulse beacon.

889
00:56:13,454 --> 00:56:15,579
<i>There must be another way
to track the ship.</i>

890
00:56:15,664 --> 00:56:17,039
Get a read on the nav. sat.

891
00:56:17,123 --> 00:56:19,708
It's a registered transport,
you must be able to locate.

892
00:56:19,793 --> 00:56:20,751
<i>Sir?</i>

893
00:56:20,835 --> 00:56:22,711
Yes, have you found a nav. sat. trajectory?

894
00:56:22,795 --> 00:56:25,213
<i>Sir, we found seven.</i>

895
00:56:32,931 --> 00:56:34,639
We've every reason to be afraid.

896
00:56:35,099 --> 00:56:38,061
Why, 'cause this guy beat up Mal?
That ain't so hard.

897
00:56:38,144 --> 00:56:40,688
He didn't beat me up.
Nobody said that.

898
00:56:40,773 --> 00:56:42,523
Because he's a believer.

899
00:56:42,775 --> 00:56:47,195
He's intelligent, methodical,
and devout in his belief

900
00:56:47,278 --> 00:56:49,655
that killing River is the right thing to do.

901
00:56:49,739 --> 00:56:51,724
So no hope of a reward?

902
00:56:53,242 --> 00:56:56,661
Did he say anything about a Miranda?

903
00:56:57,498 --> 00:56:58,539
What is that?

904
00:56:58,623 --> 00:57:01,000
Don't know who or what,
but it's on River's mind.

905
00:57:01,085 --> 00:57:03,085
Conjure it might be the reason
they're after her.

906
00:57:03,170 --> 00:57:06,047
You think maybe it poses some kind
of threat to the Alliance?

907
00:57:06,130 --> 00:57:07,507
Do we care?

908
00:57:07,882 --> 00:57:09,592
Are we caring about that?

909
00:57:09,675 --> 00:57:10,519
You dumb-ass hogs,

910
00:57:10,545 --> 00:57:13,688
the only people she's a threat
to is us on this boat.

911
00:57:13,972 --> 00:57:16,014
Look, we get back to Haven
in a few hours' time.

912
00:57:16,099 --> 00:57:18,266
Oh, yeah. Hiding under the Shepherd's skirts

913
00:57:18,351 --> 00:57:19,351
that's a manful scheme.

914
00:57:19,436 --> 00:57:20,478
You wanna run this ship?

915
00:57:20,561 --> 00:57:21,561
Yes.

916
00:57:22,523 --> 00:57:24,356
Well, you can't.

917
00:57:25,067 --> 00:57:27,275
Do a damn sight better job than you.

918
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:29,820
Getting us lashed over a couple of strays.

919
00:57:30,030 --> 00:57:32,030
No offense, Doc.
I think it's noble as a grape,

920
00:57:32,115 --> 00:57:33,324
the way you look to River.

921
00:57:33,407 --> 00:57:35,867
But she ain't my sister
and she ain't your crew.

922
00:57:35,952 --> 00:57:38,329
Oh, and neither is she exactly helpless.

923
00:57:38,704 --> 00:57:41,206
So where's it writ that we got to lay down
our lives for her?

924
00:57:41,291 --> 00:57:42,851
Which is what you've steered us toward.

925
00:57:42,918 --> 00:57:44,469
I didn't start this.

926
00:57:45,253 --> 00:57:46,838
No, that's right.

927
00:57:47,672 --> 00:57:49,269
Alliance starts the war,

928
00:57:49,494 --> 00:57:51,365
and then you volunteer.

929
00:57:53,262 --> 00:57:54,971
Battle of Serenity, Mal.

930
00:57:55,054 --> 00:57:58,166
Besides Zoe here, how many...
Hey, I'm talking at you.

931
00:58:02,311 --> 00:58:05,255
How many men in your platoon
came out of there alive?

932
00:58:08,568 --> 00:58:10,735
You wanna leave this room.

933
00:58:13,574 --> 00:58:15,282
Damn right, I do.

934
00:58:22,623 --> 00:58:24,666
This isn't the war, Mal.

935
00:58:25,543 --> 00:58:27,753
You telling me that 'cause you think
I don't know?

936
00:58:27,838 --> 00:58:29,963
You came to the Training House
looking for a fight.

937
00:58:30,047 --> 00:58:31,623
I came looking for you.

938
00:58:33,260 --> 00:58:35,677
I just want to know who I'm dealing with.

939
00:58:35,762 --> 00:58:38,231
I've seen too many versions
of you to be sure.

940
00:58:38,681 --> 00:58:40,260
I start fighting a war,

941
00:58:40,885 --> 00:58:43,059
I guarantee you'll see something new.

942
00:58:50,110 --> 00:58:51,318
We'll get off.

943
00:58:51,402 --> 00:58:53,028
River and I will get off at Haven.

944
00:58:53,112 --> 00:58:54,864
We'll find some...
Nobody's saying that.

945
00:58:54,947 --> 00:58:56,740
Nobody besides Jayne is saying that.

946
00:58:56,824 --> 00:58:57,824
Mal.

947
00:59:00,329 --> 00:59:02,103
I got no answers for you, Inara.

948
00:59:02,327 --> 00:59:03,438
I got no rudder.

949
00:59:03,498 --> 00:59:05,472
Wind blows northerly, I go north.

950
00:59:05,496 --> 00:59:06,483
That's who I am.

951
00:59:06,543 --> 00:59:09,085
Now maybe that ain't a man to lead,
but they have to follow.

952
00:59:09,170 --> 00:59:10,253
So you wanna tear me down,

953
00:59:10,338 --> 00:59:12,505
do it inside your own mind.
I'm not trying to tear you down.

954
00:59:12,590 --> 00:59:14,175
But you fog things up.

955
00:59:14,967 --> 00:59:16,277
You always have.

956
00:59:18,304 --> 00:59:19,764
You spin me about.

957
00:59:22,976 --> 00:59:25,101
I wish like hell you was elsewhere.

958
00:59:27,313 --> 00:59:28,438
I was.

959
01:01:01,574 --> 01:01:03,826
No trouble, little crazy person.

960
01:01:05,829 --> 01:01:09,206
We're going for a nice shuttle ride.

961
01:01:26,724 --> 01:01:28,516
She's out. Jayne's down.

962
01:01:28,726 --> 01:01:31,269
The other way.
Find her and do not engage.

963
01:01:53,626 --> 01:01:55,126
It's gonna be okay...

964
01:02:05,722 --> 01:02:07,889
She's sealed off the bridge.
I do not like her there.

965
01:02:07,974 --> 01:02:09,653
Check the shuttle.
She could have snuck in.

966
01:02:09,726 --> 01:02:10,726
Captain.

967
01:02:56,773 --> 01:02:59,692
The government's man,
he says you're a danger to us.

968
01:03:00,693 --> 01:03:02,318
Not worth helping.

969
01:03:04,905 --> 01:03:06,072
Is he right?

970
01:03:07,367 --> 01:03:09,784
Are you anything but a weapon?

971
01:03:12,998 --> 01:03:16,083
I've staked my crew's life on the theory
you're a person,

972
01:03:16,168 --> 01:03:19,494
actual and whole, and if I'm wrong,
you'd best shoot me now.

973
01:03:20,505 --> 01:03:22,380
Or we could talk more.

974
01:03:33,518 --> 01:03:34,601
Miranda.

975
01:03:38,731 --> 01:03:41,108
How can it be there's a whole planet
called Miranda

976
01:03:41,193 --> 01:03:42,443
and none of us knowed that?

977
01:03:42,527 --> 01:03:44,731
Because there isn't one.
It's a blackrock.

978
01:03:44,755 --> 01:03:45,927
Uninhabitable.

979
01:03:46,405 --> 01:03:49,349
Terraforming didn't hold, or some such.
Few settlers died.

980
01:03:49,534 --> 01:03:50,992
Was it right before the war?

981
01:03:51,077 --> 01:03:52,329
I had to show them.

982
01:03:52,554 --> 01:03:54,878
I didn't know if you were
going to make me sleep.

983
01:03:56,583 --> 01:03:57,625
You could have asked.

984
01:03:57,708 --> 01:03:58,791
Wait a tick, yeah.

985
01:03:58,876 --> 01:04:02,463
Some years back, there was call
for workers to settle on Miranda.

986
01:04:02,588 --> 01:04:04,340
Daddy talked about it.
Nothing about it on the Cortex.

987
01:04:04,423 --> 01:04:06,425
History, Astronomy, it's not in there.

988
01:04:06,510 --> 01:04:08,844
Half of writing history is hiding the truth.

989
01:04:08,929 --> 01:04:11,847
There's something on that rock
the Alliance doesn't want known.

990
01:04:11,931 --> 01:04:14,172
That's right at the edge
of the Burnham Quadrant, right?

991
01:04:14,184 --> 01:04:16,518
Furthest planet out?
It's not that far from here.

992
01:04:16,603 --> 01:04:18,311
Whoa. No. No. Honey...
That's a bad notion.

993
01:04:18,438 --> 01:04:19,572
You show them the bad.
I got it, baby.

994
01:04:24,443 --> 01:04:27,112
This is us at Haven, and here's Miranda.

995
01:04:27,655 --> 01:04:31,867
All along here, that empty space in between,
that's Reaver territory.

996
01:04:31,952 --> 01:04:34,577
They just float out there,
sending out raiding parties.

997
01:04:34,663 --> 01:04:36,996
Nobody ventures there.
Not even the Alliance.

998
01:04:37,081 --> 01:04:39,333
You go through that,
you're signing up to be a banquet.

999
01:04:39,416 --> 01:04:42,001
I'm on board with our standard
run-and-hide scenario.

1000
01:04:42,086 --> 01:04:43,795
And we are just about...

1001
01:04:44,630 --> 01:04:45,630
Wait.

1002
01:05:02,983 --> 01:05:04,233
Doesn't look like Reavers.

1003
01:05:04,317 --> 01:05:05,342
Wasn't.

1004
01:05:10,990 --> 01:05:11,990
Shepherd?

1005
01:05:13,784 --> 01:05:14,809
Shepherd?

1006
01:05:16,246 --> 01:05:17,496
Shepherd Book?

1007
01:05:38,559 --> 01:05:40,018
Get the Doc.

1008
01:05:41,228 --> 01:05:42,271
Shepherd.

1009
01:05:43,523 --> 01:05:44,606
Don't move.

1010
01:05:44,690 --> 01:05:46,358
Won't go far.

1011
01:05:48,987 --> 01:05:50,987
Shouldn't have been you.

1012
01:05:51,780 --> 01:05:54,307
Alliance should've hit us.
Should've hit me.

1013
01:05:55,784 --> 01:05:57,536
That crossed my mind.

1014
01:06:02,041 --> 01:06:03,458
I shot him down.

1015
01:06:03,543 --> 01:06:05,210
Yeah. I see.

1016
01:06:05,420 --> 01:06:08,005
I killed the ship that killed us.

1017
01:06:09,715 --> 01:06:11,717
Not very Christian of me.

1018
01:06:12,177 --> 01:06:13,719
You did what's right.

1019
01:06:14,179 --> 01:06:18,222
Coming from you,
that means almost nothing.

1020
01:06:23,563 --> 01:06:24,646
I'm long gone.

1021
01:06:24,731 --> 01:06:26,356
No, Doc will bring you around.

1022
01:06:26,440 --> 01:06:29,318
I look to be bored by many more
sermons before you slip.

1023
01:06:29,402 --> 01:06:30,693
Just don't move.

1024
01:06:31,278 --> 01:06:33,072
Can't order me around, boy.

1025
01:06:34,407 --> 01:06:36,157
I'm not one of your crew.

1026
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:39,661
Yes, you are.

1027
01:06:42,498 --> 01:06:44,375
River...
Come on.

1028
01:06:44,793 --> 01:06:45,793
Hey.

1029
01:06:47,586 --> 01:06:50,063
I don't care what you believe.

1030
01:06:50,288 --> 01:06:51,771
Just believe it.

1031
01:06:53,217 --> 01:06:54,809
Whatever you...

1032
01:07:28,460 --> 01:07:30,204
How come they ain't waiting?

1033
01:07:31,672 --> 01:07:34,132
They knowed we was coming,
how come they only sent one?

1034
01:07:35,802 --> 01:07:37,836
They didn't know we were coming here.

1035
01:07:38,887 --> 01:07:40,597
Get on the Cortex.

1036
01:07:40,681 --> 01:07:42,557
Wave, Li Shen, the Sanchez brothers,

1037
01:07:42,641 --> 01:07:44,601
anyone who has ever sheltered us
after a heist.

1038
01:07:44,686 --> 01:07:46,045
Tell them to get out.

1039
01:07:46,228 --> 01:07:47,478
Get out now.

1040
01:07:58,657 --> 01:07:59,824
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

1041
01:08:01,952 --> 01:08:05,706
<i>If your quarry goes to ground,
leave no ground to go to.</i>

1042
01:08:06,833 --> 01:08:08,876
<i>You should have taken my offer.</i>

1043
01:08:08,960 --> 01:08:11,503
<i>Or did you think none
of this was your fault?</i>

1044
01:08:11,795 --> 01:08:13,755
I don't murder children.

1045
01:08:14,173 --> 01:08:15,173
<i>I do.</i>

1046
01:08:16,091 --> 01:08:18,135
<i>If I have to.</i>
Why?

1047
01:08:20,012 --> 01:08:22,180
Do you even know why they sent you?

1048
01:08:22,931 --> 01:08:24,682
<i>It's not my place to ask.</i>

1049
01:08:25,894 --> 01:08:28,436
<i>I believe in something greater than myself.</i>

1050
01:08:29,564 --> 01:08:30,980
<i>A better world.</i>

1051
01:08:31,608 --> 01:08:33,442
<i>A world without sin.</i>

1052
01:08:33,984 --> 01:08:35,944
So me and mine gotta lay down and die

1053
01:08:36,029 --> 01:08:38,137
so you can live in your better world?

1054
01:08:38,698 --> 01:08:40,865
<i>I'm not going to live there.</i>

1055
01:08:41,242 --> 01:08:42,826
<i>There's no place for me there</i>

1056
01:08:42,911 --> 01:08:46,788
<i>any more than there is for you.
Malcolm, I'm a monster.</i>

1057
01:08:48,457 --> 01:08:49,750
<i>What I do is evil.</i>

1058
01:08:49,833 --> 01:08:52,377
<i>I have no illusions about it,
but it must be done.</i>

1059
01:08:52,503 --> 01:08:53,761
Keep talking.

1060
01:08:54,255 --> 01:08:56,297
You're not getting
a location trace off this wave.

1061
01:08:56,381 --> 01:09:00,202
<i>And every minute you keep River Tam
from me more people will die.</i>

1062
01:09:00,225 --> 01:09:01,427
You think I care?

1063
01:09:01,512 --> 01:09:02,887
<i>Of course you care.</i>

1064
01:09:03,806 --> 01:09:05,457
<i>You're not a Reaver, Mal.</i>

1065
01:09:06,059 --> 01:09:09,560
<i>You're a human man and you
will never understand how...</i>

1066
01:09:15,819 --> 01:09:17,610
Get these bodies together.

1067
01:09:18,112 --> 01:09:19,404
We got time for grave digging?

1068
01:09:19,488 --> 01:09:20,823
Zoe, you and Simon rope them together.

1069
01:09:20,907 --> 01:09:23,617
Five or six of them.
I want them laid out on the nose of our ship.

1070
01:09:23,701 --> 01:09:25,993
Are you insane?
I won't desecrate these bodies.

1071
01:09:26,078 --> 01:09:27,912
I don't understand.
What do you mean, the bodies...

1072
01:09:27,997 --> 01:09:29,516
I want you to muck up the reactor core.

1073
01:09:29,541 --> 01:09:31,542
Just enough to leave a trail
and make it read like

1074
01:09:31,626 --> 01:09:33,787
we're flying without containment,
not enough to fry us.

1075
01:09:33,877 --> 01:09:35,671
These people are our friends.
Kaylee,

1076
01:09:35,755 --> 01:09:38,590
you got a day's work to do
and two hours to do it.

1077
01:09:39,591 --> 01:09:43,845
Jayne, you and Wash hoist up the cannon mount.
Goes right on top.

1078
01:09:43,930 --> 01:09:45,649
Piece or two of the other ship, stick it on.

1079
01:09:45,681 --> 01:09:48,934
Any place you can tear hull without
inner breach, do that, too.

1080
01:09:49,769 --> 01:09:51,145
We're gonna need paint.

1081
01:09:51,270 --> 01:09:53,128
We're gonna need red paint.

1082
01:09:53,523 --> 01:09:54,523
Sir,

1083
01:09:54,983 --> 01:09:58,402
do you really mean to turn our home
into an abomination

1084
01:09:58,485 --> 01:10:00,319
so that we can make a suicidal attempt

1085
01:10:00,404 --> 01:10:02,447
at passing through Reaver space?

1086
01:10:02,532 --> 01:10:03,823
I mean to live.

1087
01:10:04,283 --> 01:10:05,701
I mean for us to live.

1088
01:10:05,784 --> 01:10:08,328
The Alliance won't have that,
so we go where they don't follow.

1089
01:10:08,412 --> 01:10:10,581
God's balls, there ain't no way
we're going out there.

1090
01:10:10,664 --> 01:10:11,998
Think about what you're asking.

1091
01:10:12,082 --> 01:10:14,251
Those Reavers'll eat us alive...

1092
01:10:16,378 --> 01:10:17,796
This is how it is.

1093
01:10:18,213 --> 01:10:19,894
Anybody doesn't wanna fly
with me anymore,

1094
01:10:19,966 --> 01:10:21,800
this is your port of harbor.

1095
01:10:22,676 --> 01:10:24,720
There's a lot of fine ways to die.

1096
01:10:24,804 --> 01:10:27,514
I ain't waiting for the Alliance
to choose mine.

1097
01:10:31,101 --> 01:10:34,270
I mean to confound these bungers.
Take my shot at getting to Miranda.

1098
01:10:34,354 --> 01:10:36,899
Maybe find something
I can use to get clear of this.

1099
01:10:36,983 --> 01:10:39,902
So I hear a word out of any of you
that ain't helping me out

1100
01:10:39,985 --> 01:10:42,487
or taking your leave,
I will shoot you down.

1101
01:10:47,452 --> 01:10:48,784
Get to work.

1102
01:11:13,936 --> 01:11:14,936
Sir...

1103
01:11:15,020 --> 01:11:16,563
Just tell me when we're close.

1104
01:12:24,465 --> 01:12:25,465
Wash.

1105
01:13:30,113 --> 01:13:33,324
Define disappeared.

1106
01:13:38,081 --> 01:13:40,332
Every reading I'm getting says normal.

1107
01:13:41,042 --> 01:13:44,377
Oceans, land masses.
No tectonic instability or radiation.

1108
01:13:44,462 --> 01:13:46,046
Yeah, but no power, either.

1109
01:13:46,130 --> 01:13:47,421
Nothing at all?

1110
01:13:47,506 --> 01:13:48,506
Wait.

1111
01:13:49,175 --> 01:13:50,300
Something.

1112
01:13:51,344 --> 01:13:53,845
It might be a beacon, but it's awful weak.

1113
01:13:54,514 --> 01:13:55,930
Find it.

1114
01:14:04,231 --> 01:14:05,856
<i>Gravity's Earthnorm.</i>

1115
01:14:06,525 --> 01:14:08,734
<i>O2 levels check, pressure...</i>

1116
01:14:09,529 --> 01:14:11,764
<i>If anything's wrong the scanner's
not reading it.</i>

1117
01:14:18,203 --> 01:14:20,579
Well, something sure the hell ain't right.

1118
01:14:23,542 --> 01:14:24,823
This ain't no little settlement.

1119
01:14:24,877 --> 01:14:27,612
<i>We flew over at least
a dozen cities just as big.</i>

1120
01:14:27,796 --> 01:14:29,965
<i>Why didn't we ever hear about this?</i>

1121
01:14:32,051 --> 01:14:33,426
Beacon's up ahead.

1122
01:14:56,492 --> 01:14:57,492
Ho.

1123
01:15:17,555 --> 01:15:19,930
No entry wounds, fractures.

1124
01:15:20,390 --> 01:15:21,600
Poison?

1125
01:15:34,238 --> 01:15:35,863
Got another one.

1126
01:15:41,453 --> 01:15:43,162
They's just sitting here.

1127
01:15:44,873 --> 01:15:46,123
They didn't crash.

1128
01:16:00,680 --> 01:16:02,224
Kaylee. Don't...

1129
01:16:07,979 --> 01:16:10,231
How come these ones are preserved?

1130
01:16:10,774 --> 01:16:12,900
Place must've gone hermetic
when the power blew.

1131
01:16:12,984 --> 01:16:14,109
Sealed them.

1132
01:16:14,194 --> 01:16:15,654
What are they doing?

1133
01:16:16,822 --> 01:16:18,739
What's everybody doing?

1134
01:16:18,990 --> 01:16:21,451
There's no unusual discoloration.

1135
01:16:21,993 --> 01:16:24,703
Nobody's doubled over
or showing signs of pain.

1136
01:16:25,163 --> 01:16:27,498
There's gasses that kill painless, right?

1137
01:16:27,750 --> 01:16:30,167
They didn't fall.
None of them.

1138
01:16:30,543 --> 01:16:32,295
They just lay down.

1139
01:16:36,050 --> 01:16:39,301
Make them stop.
They're everywhere.

1140
01:16:40,220 --> 01:16:42,346
Every city, every...

1141
01:16:42,640 --> 01:16:45,516
Every house, every room,
they're all inside me.

1142
01:16:45,643 --> 01:16:49,061
I can hear them all,
and they're saying nothing!

1143
01:16:50,105 --> 01:16:51,105
Get up.

1144
01:16:52,190 --> 01:16:53,692
Please get up.

1145
01:16:58,488 --> 01:17:00,681
Please, God, make me a stone.

1146
01:17:01,993 --> 01:17:03,827
She is starting to damage my calm.

1147
01:17:03,911 --> 01:17:05,412
Jayne.
She's right!

1148
01:17:06,413 --> 01:17:08,038
Everybody's dead.

1149
01:17:09,542 --> 01:17:11,835
This whole world is dead for no reason!

1150
01:17:14,255 --> 01:17:16,171
Let's get to the beacon.

1151
01:17:42,240 --> 01:17:44,158
This is the source?

1152
01:17:47,496 --> 01:17:49,747
This ship's banged up all to hell.

1153
01:18:06,974 --> 01:18:09,768
<i>These are just a few of the images
we've recorded.</i>

1154
01:18:10,853 --> 01:18:12,436
<i>And you can see</i>

1155
01:18:14,105 --> 01:18:15,648
<i>it isn't what we thought.</i>

1156
01:18:17,234 --> 01:18:18,734
<i>There's been no war here,</i>

1157
01:18:19,737 --> 01:18:22,822
<i>and no terraforming event.
The environment is stable.</i>

1158
01:18:27,953 --> 01:18:29,371
<i>It's the Pax.</i>

1159
01:18:30,872 --> 01:18:35,210
<i>The G-23 Paxilon Hydroclorate
that we added to the air processors.</i>

1160
01:18:36,170 --> 01:18:39,922
<i>It was supposed to calm the population,
weed out aggression.</i>

1161
01:18:42,009 --> 01:18:43,635
<i>Well, it works.</i>

1162
01:18:44,552 --> 01:18:46,970
<i>The people here stopped fighting.</i>

1163
01:18:47,972 --> 01:18:50,600
<i>And then they stopped everything else.</i>

1164
01:18:55,480 --> 01:18:57,689
<i>They stopped going to work,</i>

1165
01:18:58,567 --> 01:19:02,820
<i>they stopped breeding, talking, eating.</i>

1166
01:19:04,657 --> 01:19:08,210
<i>There's 30 million people here,
and they all just let themselves die.</i>

1167
01:19:11,997 --> 01:19:13,414
<i>I have to be quick.</i>

1168
01:19:14,542 --> 01:19:19,253
<i>About a tenth of a percent of the population
had the opposite reaction to the Pax.</i>

1169
01:19:19,255 --> 01:19:22,923
<i>Their aggressor response increased
beyond madness.</i>

1170
01:19:23,341 --> 01:19:24,551
<i>They have become...</i>

1171
01:19:26,929 --> 01:19:28,595
<i>Well, they've killed most of us.</i>

1172
01:19:29,681 --> 01:19:31,432
<i>And not just killed,</i>

1173
01:19:33,269 --> 01:19:35,019
<i>they've done things.</i>

1174
01:19:35,520 --> 01:19:36,534
Reavers.

1175
01:19:37,060 --> 01:19:38,814
They made them.

1176
01:19:40,275 --> 01:19:42,216
<i>I won't live to report this,</i>

1177
01:19:42,440 --> 01:19:44,427
<i>but people have to know.</i>

1178
01:19:45,698 --> 01:19:47,489
<i>We meant it for the best,</i>

1179
01:19:47,992 --> 01:19:49,074
<i>to make people safer.</i>

1180
01:19:51,162 --> 01:19:54,204
<i>God!</i>

1181
01:19:59,043 --> 01:20:00,920
Turn it off.

1182
01:20:25,613 --> 01:20:26,820
River.

1183
01:20:26,905 --> 01:20:28,298
I'm all right.

1184
01:20:35,997 --> 01:20:37,497
I'm all right.

1185
01:20:46,257 --> 01:20:48,318
This report is maybe 12 years old.

1186
01:20:49,720 --> 01:20:53,297
Parliament buried it,
and it stayed buried till River dug it up.

1187
01:20:55,225 --> 01:20:57,444
This is what they feared she knew.

1188
01:20:58,270 --> 01:21:00,104
And they were right to fear,

1189
01:21:00,648 --> 01:21:03,649
because there's a whole universe of folk
who are gonna know it, too.

1190
01:21:03,734 --> 01:21:05,359
They're gonna see it.

1191
01:21:05,944 --> 01:21:08,613
Somebody has to speak for these people.

1192
01:21:12,033 --> 01:21:14,368
You all got on this boat for different reasons,

1193
01:21:14,453 --> 01:21:16,621
but you all come to the same place.

1194
01:21:17,081 --> 01:21:20,250
So now I'm asking more
of you than I have before.

1195
01:21:21,377 --> 01:21:22,710
Maybe all.

1196
01:21:24,671 --> 01:21:27,881
Sure as I know anything I know this,
they will try again.

1197
01:21:29,260 --> 01:21:31,719
Maybe on another world,
maybe on this very ground swept clean.

1198
01:21:31,804 --> 01:21:34,639
A year from now, 10,
they'll swing back to the belief

1199
01:21:34,806 --> 01:21:36,890
that they can make people...

1200
01:21:39,603 --> 01:21:40,603
better.

1201
01:21:43,774 --> 01:21:45,817
And I do not hold to that.

1202
01:21:48,153 --> 01:21:49,570
So no more running.

1203
01:21:52,115 --> 01:21:53,824
I aim to misbehave.

1204
01:22:01,625 --> 01:22:03,876
Shepherd Book used to tell me,

1205
01:22:03,961 --> 01:22:06,003
If you can't do something smart,

1206
01:22:07,547 --> 01:22:09,340
do something right.

1207
01:22:10,634 --> 01:22:11,842
Do we have a plan?

1208
01:22:11,926 --> 01:22:13,344
Mr. Universe.

1209
01:22:13,929 --> 01:22:15,930
We haven't the equipment
to broadwave this code,

1210
01:22:16,015 --> 01:22:18,515
but he can put it on every screen for 30 worlds.

1211
01:22:19,100 --> 01:22:20,851
He's pretty damn close, too.

1212
01:22:21,395 --> 01:22:22,520
We still got the Reavers

1213
01:22:22,604 --> 01:22:24,855
and probably the Alliance,
between us and him.

1214
01:22:25,149 --> 01:22:27,859
That's two armies against our
one bitty cannon.

1215
01:22:28,027 --> 01:22:30,828
It's a fair bet the Alliance knows
about Mr. Universe.

1216
01:22:31,113 --> 01:22:32,572
They're gonna see this coming.

1217
01:22:33,698 --> 01:22:34,698
No.

1218
01:22:36,743 --> 01:22:39,078
They're not gonna see this coming.

1219
01:22:47,378 --> 01:22:49,338
<i>No problem. Bring it on.
Bring it on. Bring it on.</i>

1220
01:22:49,715 --> 01:22:52,341
<i>From here to the eyes and ears of the 'verse.
That's my motto,</i>

1221
01:22:52,426 --> 01:22:54,801
<i>or it might be, if I start having a motto.</i>

1222
01:22:54,886 --> 01:22:55,927
We won't be long.

1223
01:22:56,012 --> 01:22:57,971
<i>You're going to get caught in the ion cloud.</i>

1224
01:22:58,056 --> 01:22:59,681
<i>It'll play merry hob with your radar,</i>

1225
01:22:59,766 --> 01:23:02,644
<i>but pretty lights and a few miles after,
you'll be right in my orbit.</i>

1226
01:23:02,728 --> 01:23:04,895
You'll let us know if anyone else comes at you?

1227
01:23:04,979 --> 01:23:06,430
You'll be the first.

1228
01:23:12,779 --> 01:23:13,988
There.

1229
01:23:14,198 --> 01:23:16,239
Toss me my 30 coin,
but I got a news wave for you...

1230
01:23:26,627 --> 01:23:29,753
Call in every ship in the quadrant.
We'll meet them in the air.

1231
01:23:31,381 --> 01:23:32,923
Destroy it all.

1232
01:23:59,618 --> 01:24:02,036
Wash, we almost through?

1233
01:24:24,059 --> 01:24:25,059
Now!

1234
01:24:30,606 --> 01:24:32,274
Go! Move!

1235
01:24:51,962 --> 01:24:54,005
I'm reading activity in the cloud.

1236
01:24:54,088 --> 01:24:56,131
Lock and fire on my command.

1237
01:24:58,260 --> 01:25:00,552
You should have let me see her, Captain.

1238
01:25:01,680 --> 01:25:03,337
We should have done this as men.

1239
01:25:04,261 --> 01:25:05,640
Not with fire.

1240
01:25:05,768 --> 01:25:06,768
Sir.

1241
01:25:12,274 --> 01:25:14,024
Vessel in range.
Lock on.

1242
01:25:21,949 --> 01:25:23,868
Bastard's not even changing course.

1243
01:25:29,041 --> 01:25:30,041
Sir!

1244
01:25:33,670 --> 01:25:34,836
Target the Reavers.

1245
01:25:35,161 --> 01:25:36,680
Target the Reavers!

1246
01:25:36,840 --> 01:25:39,132
Target everyone!
Somebody fire!

1247
01:25:56,693 --> 01:25:58,289
I am a leaf on the wind.

1248
01:25:59,114 --> 01:26:01,011
Watch how I soar.

1249
01:26:15,420 --> 01:26:17,087
Chicken's come home to roost.

1250
01:26:18,590 --> 01:26:20,274
The hell?
It's okay.

1251
01:26:20,842 --> 01:26:21,842
I am a leaf on the wind!

1252
01:26:21,926 --> 01:26:23,219
What does that mean?

1253
01:26:27,431 --> 01:26:28,932
We're almost through.

1254
01:26:45,617 --> 01:26:48,034
No! No! No!
Yes! Yes!

1255
01:27:41,006 --> 01:27:42,506
We're not alone.

1256
01:27:49,221 --> 01:27:50,347
EMP!

1257
01:27:51,224 --> 01:27:52,975
Everybody, strap yourselves into something!

1258
01:27:53,060 --> 01:27:54,060
Jayne.
Got it.

1259
01:27:55,395 --> 01:27:57,145
Kaylee, come on.

1260
01:28:09,909 --> 01:28:11,284
We're fried.
I got no control.

1261
01:28:11,369 --> 01:28:12,752
Where's the backup?

1262
01:28:12,877 --> 01:28:14,337
Where's the backup?

1263
01:28:22,296 --> 01:28:23,672
Check! Check!

1264
01:28:48,073 --> 01:28:49,198
Get up!

1265
01:28:49,282 --> 01:28:50,323
Stop it!

1266
01:28:55,913 --> 01:28:57,998
Backup reads at 20%.
Can you get us down?

1267
01:28:58,082 --> 01:28:59,404
I'm going to have to glide her in.

1268
01:28:59,417 --> 01:29:01,167
Will that work?

1269
01:29:55,931 --> 01:29:57,640
I am a leaf on the wind.

1270
01:29:59,853 --> 01:30:00,895
Watch how...

1271
01:30:03,939 --> 01:30:06,399
Wash, baby. Baby, no.

1272
01:30:06,400 --> 01:30:08,326
Baby, come on. You gotta go.
Come on.

1273
01:30:08,487 --> 01:30:09,404
We gotta move.

1274
01:30:09,429 --> 01:30:12,079
Baby, please. We gotta
move, baby, come on.

1275
01:30:14,894 --> 01:30:16,194
Come on.
Zoe!

1276
01:30:17,746 --> 01:30:19,662
Move out! Now!

1277
01:30:23,502 --> 01:30:24,542
Go. Go.

1278
01:30:25,212 --> 01:30:26,545
Head inside!

1279
01:30:45,649 --> 01:30:47,233
Jayne, rearguard.

1280
01:30:54,865 --> 01:30:55,824
Zoe, what've we got?

1281
01:30:55,908 --> 01:30:56,934
Sir,

1282
01:30:59,037 --> 01:31:00,287
this is a good hold point.

1283
01:31:00,622 --> 01:31:02,247
We all stay together.
No.

1284
01:31:02,332 --> 01:31:03,572
They have to come through here.

1285
01:31:03,582 --> 01:31:05,542
They'll bottleneck, we can thin them out.

1286
01:31:05,627 --> 01:31:08,420
We get pushed back,
there's the blast doors.

1287
01:31:08,546 --> 01:31:10,881
I can rig them so they won't reopen
once they close.

1288
01:31:10,966 --> 01:31:11,966
Shut them and hide until I get...

1289
01:31:12,050 --> 01:31:14,009
We need to draw them till it's done.

1290
01:31:15,136 --> 01:31:17,512
This is the place.
We'll buy you the time.

1291
01:31:22,394 --> 01:31:24,712
All right, let's move these crates
back there for cover.

1292
01:31:24,895 --> 01:31:27,230
Make sure they ain't filled
with nothing goes boom.

1293
01:31:27,690 --> 01:31:29,733
Wait, Wash! Where's Wash?

1294
01:31:30,860 --> 01:31:32,444
He ain't coming.

1295
01:31:37,576 --> 01:31:39,359
Move the gorramn crates!

1296
01:31:57,345 --> 01:31:59,146
Tell me you brought them this time.

1297
01:32:22,578 --> 01:32:23,828
Zoe?

1298
01:32:25,998 --> 01:32:27,416
Are you here?

1299
01:32:27,500 --> 01:32:28,626
Do the job, sir.

1300
01:32:31,212 --> 01:32:33,838
You hold.
Hold till I get back.

1301
01:32:37,927 --> 01:32:38,969
Captain's right.

1302
01:32:39,054 --> 01:32:41,756
Can't be thinking on revenge
if we're gonna get through this.

1303
01:32:42,140 --> 01:32:44,667
Do you really think any of us
are gonna get through this?

1304
01:32:48,313 --> 01:32:49,354
I might.

1305
01:33:06,413 --> 01:33:07,413
No.

1306
01:33:28,979 --> 01:33:29,979
Mal.

1307
01:33:30,854 --> 01:33:32,564
Guy killed me, Mal.

1308
01:33:32,983 --> 01:33:36,193
He killed me with a sword.
How weird is that?

1309
01:33:37,069 --> 01:33:40,989
I got a short span here.

1310
01:33:42,449 --> 01:33:44,201
They destroyed my equipment,

1311
01:33:44,536 --> 01:33:46,119
but I have a backup unit.

1312
01:33:46,203 --> 01:33:48,579
Bottom of the complex,
right over the generator.

1313
01:33:49,039 --> 01:33:52,208
Hard to get to.
I know they missed it.

1314
01:33:53,002 --> 01:33:55,212
They can't stop the signal, Mal.

1315
01:33:56,088 --> 01:33:58,506
They can never stop the signal.

1316
01:34:02,720 --> 01:34:05,096
The Reavers.
They are all made up of rage.

1317
01:34:05,180 --> 01:34:06,222
It's okay.
It's okay.

1318
01:34:06,265 --> 01:34:07,875
I can't shut them up.

1319
01:34:11,729 --> 01:34:12,895
Stay low.

1320
01:34:13,480 --> 01:34:16,841
She picked a sweet bung of a time
to go helpless on us.

1321
01:34:18,110 --> 01:34:19,350
Jayne and I take the first wave.

1322
01:34:19,362 --> 01:34:21,505
Nobody shoots unless they get past our fire.

1323
01:34:25,702 --> 01:34:28,328
I didn't plan on going out like this.

1324
01:34:30,164 --> 01:34:31,815
I think we did right, but...

1325
01:34:34,560 --> 01:34:36,012
No. I never planned...

1326
01:34:36,537 --> 01:34:37,878
anything.

1327
01:34:39,716 --> 01:34:41,725
I just wanted to keep River safe.

1328
01:34:45,680 --> 01:34:49,350
Spent so much time on Serenity
ignoring anything

1329
01:34:50,310 --> 01:34:52,810
that I wanted for myself.

1330
01:34:57,567 --> 01:34:59,943
My one regret in all of this...

1331
01:35:01,237 --> 01:35:02,945
is never being with you.

1332
01:35:05,074 --> 01:35:06,408
With me?

1333
01:35:08,161 --> 01:35:10,162
You mean to say, as...

1334
01:35:12,122 --> 01:35:13,247
Sex?

1335
01:35:15,502 --> 01:35:17,293
I mean to say.

1336
01:35:22,257 --> 01:35:23,623
Hell with this.

1337
01:35:23,748 --> 01:35:25,409
I'm gonna live.

1338
01:35:39,317 --> 01:35:40,251
Mal.

1339
01:35:40,475 --> 01:35:42,676
Guy killed me, Mal.

1340
01:35:43,738 --> 01:35:45,405
He killed me with a sword.

1341
01:36:24,112 --> 01:36:25,695
Hard to get to.

1342
01:36:27,030 --> 01:36:28,698
That's a fact.

1343
01:36:35,998 --> 01:36:37,498
Zoe, gorrammit!

1344
01:36:53,349 --> 01:36:55,684
Zoe, get your ass back on the line!

1345
01:37:12,202 --> 01:37:13,911
You shot me in the back!

1346
01:37:15,537 --> 01:37:17,997
I haven't made you angry, have I?

1347
01:37:18,082 --> 01:37:21,167
There are a lot of innocent people
in the air being killed right now.

1348
01:37:21,252 --> 01:37:23,712
You have no idea how true that is.

1349
01:37:25,172 --> 01:37:26,840
I know the secret.

1350
01:37:27,591 --> 01:37:30,051
The truth that burned up River Tam's brain.

1351
01:37:30,845 --> 01:37:32,631
Rest of the 'verse is going to know it, too.

1352
01:37:33,657 --> 01:37:34,956
'Cause they need to.

1353
01:37:36,809 --> 01:37:38,411
Do you really believe that?

1354
01:37:39,395 --> 01:37:40,520
I do.

1355
01:37:40,604 --> 01:37:42,730
You willing to die for that belief?

1356
01:37:45,109 --> 01:37:46,275
I am.

1357
01:37:53,076 --> 01:37:55,118
Of course, that ain't exactly Plan A.

1358
01:38:21,645 --> 01:38:22,688
Spine's intact.

1359
01:38:22,771 --> 01:38:23,939
Just give me a bandage.

1360
01:39:17,534 --> 01:39:18,993
Up high, left!

1361
01:39:26,711 --> 01:39:27,869
Kaylee!

1362
01:39:40,850 --> 01:39:44,670
Fall back! Everybody, fall back!
Fall back now!

1363
01:39:54,363 --> 01:39:55,655
Jayne, grenade.

1364
01:39:57,033 --> 01:39:59,242
Very last one.

1365
01:40:05,248 --> 01:40:06,332
They're gonna get in.

1366
01:40:06,708 --> 01:40:09,418
I can close it from the outside.

1367
01:40:09,796 --> 01:40:11,697
No one's coming back from that.

1368
01:40:14,759 --> 01:40:16,717
How much ammo do we have?

1369
01:40:16,844 --> 01:40:19,721
Three, four max, and my swinging cod.

1370
01:40:20,046 --> 01:40:21,806
That's all.
The lift isn't moving.

1371
01:40:21,890 --> 01:40:24,350
When they come,
try to plug the hole with it.

1372
01:40:24,435 --> 01:40:26,853
I'm starting to lose some feeling here.

1373
01:40:26,938 --> 01:40:29,448
Lie still.
I'm going to give you something...

1374
01:40:31,650 --> 01:40:32,650
My bag.

1375
01:40:42,994 --> 01:40:44,537
Keep pressure here.

1376
01:40:46,289 --> 01:40:47,289
My bag.

1377
01:40:47,792 --> 01:40:48,792
I need...

1378
01:40:49,627 --> 01:40:53,130
adrenaline and a shot of...

1379
01:40:53,631 --> 01:40:55,256
calaphar for Kaylee.

1380
01:40:57,969 --> 01:40:59,636
I can't.

1381
01:41:03,474 --> 01:41:04,474
River.

1382
01:41:09,604 --> 01:41:11,439
River, I'm sorry.

1383
01:41:11,524 --> 01:41:12,570
No.

1384
01:41:13,496 --> 01:41:14,524
No.

1385
01:41:21,993 --> 01:41:23,076
I hate to leave.

1386
01:41:23,161 --> 01:41:24,202
You won't.

1387
01:41:27,122 --> 01:41:29,707
You take care of me, Simon.

1388
01:41:32,837 --> 01:41:35,363
You've always taken care of me.

1389
01:41:40,802 --> 01:41:41,802
My turn.

1390
01:42:36,818 --> 01:42:38,944
Do you know what your sin is, Mal?

1391
01:42:40,070 --> 01:42:41,118
Go to hell.

1392
01:42:42,043 --> 01:42:43,430
I'm a fan of all seven.

1393
01:42:49,913 --> 01:42:51,265
But right now,

1394
01:42:52,750 --> 01:42:54,751
I'm going to have to go with wrath.

1395
01:42:59,215 --> 01:43:01,074
We ain't got long.

1396
01:43:07,681 --> 01:43:09,599
You suppose he got through?

1397
01:43:10,851 --> 01:43:12,810
Do you think Mal got the word out?

1398
01:43:13,479 --> 01:43:14,878
He got through.

1399
01:43:15,503 --> 01:43:17,722
I know he got through.

1400
01:43:29,161 --> 01:43:30,420
I'm sorry.

1401
01:43:33,457 --> 01:43:35,850
You should know there's no shame in this.

1402
01:43:38,462 --> 01:43:40,588
You've done remarkable things.

1403
01:43:41,798 --> 01:43:43,609
But you're fighting a war...

1404
01:43:45,176 --> 01:43:46,386
you've already lost.

1405
01:43:51,434 --> 01:43:53,143
Well, I'm known for that.

1406
01:44:02,028 --> 01:44:05,255
Piece of shrapnel tore up that nerve
cluster my first tour.

1407
01:44:06,282 --> 01:44:07,615
Had it moved.

1408
01:44:09,201 --> 01:44:10,659
Sorry about the throat.

1409
01:44:11,244 --> 01:44:14,079
Expect you'd want to say your famous
last words right now.

1410
01:44:15,166 --> 01:44:16,707
Just one trouble.

1411
01:44:21,421 --> 01:44:22,922
I ain't gonna kill you.

1412
01:44:26,426 --> 01:44:29,511
Hell, I'm gonna grant your greatest wish.

1413
01:44:36,854 --> 01:44:39,689
I'm gonna show you a world without sin.

1414
01:44:45,529 --> 01:44:48,698
<i>These are just a few of the few images
we've recorded and you can see...</i>

1415
01:44:51,618 --> 01:44:53,787
<i>it isn't what we thought.</i>

1416
01:44:55,413 --> 01:44:57,289
<i>There's been no war here,</i>

1417
01:44:58,042 --> 01:45:00,109
<i>and no terraforming event.</i>

1418
01:45:00,534 --> 01:45:02,560
<i>The environment is stable.</i>

1419
01:45:03,881 --> 01:45:05,474
<i>It's the Pax.</i>

1420
01:45:07,385 --> 01:45:11,720
<i>The G-23 Paxilon Hydroclorate that
we added to the air processors.</i>

1421
01:45:12,430 --> 01:45:14,858
<i>It was supposed to calm the population...</i>

1422
01:45:43,628 --> 01:45:45,296
<i>We meant it for the best,</i>

1423
01:45:46,215 --> 01:45:47,756
<i>to make people safer.</i>

1424
01:45:49,551 --> 01:45:50,844
<i>God!</i>

1425
01:46:13,701 --> 01:46:15,034
Sir?

1426
01:46:15,118 --> 01:46:16,161
It's done.

1427
01:46:19,372 --> 01:46:20,707
Report.

1428
01:46:22,835 --> 01:46:24,002
River?

1429
01:46:49,569 --> 01:46:50,569
<i>Drop your weapons!</i>

1430
01:46:50,654 --> 01:46:51,695
<i>Do it now.</i>

1431
01:46:51,780 --> 01:46:53,155
<i>Weapons down.
Let it down, now.</i>

1432
01:46:53,239 --> 01:46:54,823
<i>I want to see your hands in the air.</i>

1433
01:46:54,908 --> 01:46:56,784
<i>Stand down.
Do it.</i>

1434
01:47:02,207 --> 01:47:03,707
<i>Targets are acquired.</i>

1435
01:47:03,792 --> 01:47:05,167
<i>Do we have a kill order?</i>

1436
01:47:08,171 --> 01:47:09,963
<i>Do we have an order?</i>

1437
01:47:18,099 --> 01:47:19,349
<i>Stand down.</i>

1438
01:47:20,475 --> 01:47:23,228
<i>Stand down.
It's finished.</i>

1439
01:47:27,065 --> 01:47:28,440
<i>We're finished.</i>

1440
01:49:30,814 --> 01:49:32,649
It's not over, you know.

1441
01:49:34,318 --> 01:49:37,028
I can't guarantee that
they won't come after you.

1442
01:49:37,863 --> 01:49:38,863
The Parliament.

1443
01:49:39,823 --> 01:49:42,742
Your broadwave about Miranda
has weakened their regime.

1444
01:49:42,826 --> 01:49:45,735
They are not gone and they are not...

1445
01:49:46,360 --> 01:49:47,429
forgiving.

1446
01:49:47,789 --> 01:49:49,949
That don't bode especially well for you,

1447
01:49:50,960 --> 01:49:52,582
giving the order to let us go,

1448
01:49:52,707 --> 01:49:54,027
patching up our hurt.

1449
01:49:55,381 --> 01:49:57,576
I told them the Tams
were no longer a threat,

1450
01:49:57,801 --> 01:49:58,864
damage done.

1451
01:49:59,342 --> 01:50:00,643
They might listen,

1452
01:50:01,679 --> 01:50:03,412
but I think they know I'm no longer,

1453
01:50:03,936 --> 01:50:05,079
their man.

1454
01:50:06,809 --> 01:50:07,855
They take you down,

1455
01:50:07,881 --> 01:50:09,917
I don't expect to grieve over much.

1456
01:50:12,189 --> 01:50:14,207
Like to kill you myself, I see you again.

1457
01:50:15,400 --> 01:50:16,400
You won't.

1458
01:50:19,320 --> 01:50:21,131
There is nothing left to see.

1459
01:50:27,203 --> 01:50:28,746
Sir, we have a green light.

1460
01:50:29,206 --> 01:50:31,416
Inspection's pos and we're clear for up-thrust.

1461
01:50:37,881 --> 01:50:40,007
Think she'll hold together?

1462
01:50:41,010 --> 01:50:43,636
She's tore up plenty.
But she'll fly true.

1463
01:50:47,975 --> 01:50:49,725
Make sure everything's secure.

1464
01:50:52,061 --> 01:50:53,645
Could be bumpy.

1465
01:50:53,730 --> 01:50:54,980
Always is.

1466
01:51:02,405 --> 01:51:03,506
Taking her out.

1467
01:51:03,548 --> 01:51:05,591
Should be about a day's ride
to get you back to your girls.

1468
01:51:06,076 --> 01:51:07,243
Right.

1469
01:51:08,662 --> 01:51:10,872
Ready to get off this heap,
back to civilized life?

1470
01:51:10,956 --> 01:51:11,956
I...

1471
01:51:16,753 --> 01:51:18,087
